<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="896" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d896">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 EW/11–2444</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The American Representative on the United Nations War
                            Crimes Commission</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Pell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 2</seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-24">November 24,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received December 6.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that at the
                        meeting of Committee No. II, of the War Crimes Commission, held yesterday,
                        Thursday November 23, Sir Cecil Hurst, the Chairman of the Commission and
                        Commissioner for the United Kingdom, said that the British Government had
                        taken the initiative to give a directive to the Military High Command,
                        instructing them to receive our list of war criminals.</p>
                    <p>Respectfully,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Herbert Pell</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>